Project Title: Leaky Integrate-and-Fire Neuron Model

Overview

This project implements the Leaky Integrate-and-Fire (LIF) neuron model, one of the simplest and most widely used models in computational neuroscience. It simulates how neurons integrate incoming currents and fire action potentials once the membrane potential reaches a threshold.

The goal of this project is to explore how changes in input current and model parameters affect spiking behavior, and to build a foundation for understanding more complex neural models.

Features
	-	Simulates the differential equation governing the LIF model:
		τ(dV/dt) = -(V - V_rest) + R*I(t)
	-	Adjustable parameters:
	-	Membrane resistance (R)
	-	Membrane time constant (τ)
	-	Resting potential (V_rest)

INSTALLATION
1. Clone the repository:
   git clone https://github.com/dylanrdc/computational-neuro.git
   cd computational-neuro

2. (Optional) Create a virtual environment:
   python -m venv venv
   source venv/bin/activate   # macOS/Linux
   venv\Scripts\activate      # Windows

3. Install dependencies:
	- Listed at bottom

USAGE
Run the LIF neuron simulation:
   python LIF_model/lif_neuron.py

This will generate plots that show:
- Membrane potential over time
- Spike raster output

You can adjust model parameters directly in the script to see how they affect neuron behavior.

PROJECT STRUCTURE
computational-neuro/
- LIF_model/         : Python implementation of the LIF model
  - lif_neuron.py
- venv/              : Virtual environment (ignored in Git)
- README.txt
- requirements.txt

REQUIREMENTS
- Python 3.9+
- Packages: numpy, matplotlib
(All dependencies listed in requirements.txt)	-	Threshold voltage (V_th)
	-	Input current (I(t))
	-	Generates plots of membrane potential over time and spike raster output.
	-	Modular code that can be extended to networks of neurons


Installation
1. Clone the repository:
   git clone https://github.com/dylanrdc/computational-neuro.git
   cd computational-neuro

2. (Optional) Create a virtual environment:
   python -m venv venv
   source venv/bin/activate   # macOS/Linux
   venv\Scripts\activate      # Windows

3. Install dependencies:
   pip install -r requirements.txt

Use
Run the LIF neuron simulation:
   python LIF_model/lif_neuron.py

This will generate plots showing:
- Membrane potential over time
- Spike raster output

You can adjust model parameters directly in the script to see how they affect neuron behavior.

Structure
computational-neuro/
- LIF_model/         : Python implementation of the LIF model
  - lif_neuron.py
- venv/              : Virtual environment (ignored in Git)
- README.txt

Reqs
- Python 3.9+
- Packages: numpy, matplotlib

References
	-	Dayan, P., & Abbott, L. F. (2001). Theoretical Neuroscience: Computational and Mathematical Modeling of Neural Systems.
